history.content: Should be doable if you are willing to work hard!

children.subject:
Anthing is possible, but imo that schedule would be difficult unless that type of mathematical intuition comes naturally to you. I would say pick one if you are trying to achieve a certain grade/GPA level. I took both of these courses at the same time as other techs, and felt like I could never devote 100% of my attention to each class (the other courses were always pulling me away at inopportune moments). By grades suffered from this action. 

A lot of people like to take 70 in the summer because its the only thing they are doing, and thus can devote 100% of their attention to mastering the tricky subjects.

history.content: Hi, I'm trying to take Math 53 and CS70 during this summer. Do you guys think it's possible to do well in both courses? Thanks.
